de the ID of the product instance you wish to filter on.                      For example, some users may have more than one premiumaccess product, so the product_types value would be premiumaccess:1234.                      Product ID can be obtained from the GET /products response.}
@returns(200) {related_searches: [map]?, videos: [map]?, facets: map{specific_people: [map]?, events: [map]?, locations: [map]?, artists: [map]?, entertainment: [map]?}, result_count: int(int32), auto_corrections: map{phrase: str?}} # OK
